#5-plan-or-apply\",\"content\":\"Preview apply without mutating files:\"}],[\"/why\",{\"id\":\"/why\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"page\",\"content\":\"Why Boxfiles\",\"breadcrumbs\":[\"Docs\"],\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why\"}],[\"/why-0\",{\"id\":\"/why-0\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why\",\"content\":\"Why Boxfiles exists, what it optimizes for, and where it should not be used.\"}],[\"/why-1\",{\"id\":\"/why-1\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#why-boxfiles\",\"content\":\"Why Boxfiles\"}],[\"/why-2\",{\"id\":\"/why-2\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#the-problem\",\"content\":\"The problem\"}],[\"/why-3\",{\"id\":\"/why-3\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#what-boxfiles-optimizes-for\",\"content\":\"What Boxfiles optimizes for\"}],[\"/why-4\",{\"id\":\"/why-4\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#local-first-setup\",\"content\":\"Local-first setup\"}],[\"/why-5\",{\"id\":\"/why-5\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#plan-before-apply\",\"content\":\"Plan before apply\"}],[\"/why-6\",{\"id\":\"/why-6\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#small-manifests\",\"content\":\"Small manifests\"}],[\"/why-7\",{\"id\":\"/why-7\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#capability-plugins\",\"content\":\"Capability plugins\"}],[\"/why-8\",{\"id\":\"/why-8\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#why-not-just-shell-scripts\",\"content\":\"Why not just shell scripts?\"}],[\"/why-9\",{\"id\":\"/why-9\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#why-not-ansible\",\"content\":\"Why not Ansible?\"}],[\"/why-10\",{\"id\":\"/why-10\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#why-not-nix\",\"content\":\"Why not Nix?\"}],[\"/why-11\",{\"id\":\"/why-11\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#what-boxfiles-is-not\",\"content\":\"What Boxfiles is not\"}],[\"/why-12\",{\"id\":\"/why-12\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#good-fit\",\"content\":\"Good fit\"}],[\"/why-13\",{\"id\":\"/why-13\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"type\":\"heading\",\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/why#bad-fit\",\"content\":\"Bad fit\"}],[\"/why-14\",{\"id\":\"/why-14\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-boxfiles\",\"content\":\"Boxfiles is workstation provisioning with less ceremony than Ansible and less commitment than Nix.\"}],[\"/why-15\",{\"id\":\"/why-15\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-boxfiles\",\"content\":\"Use it when you want a repo of small manifests that can copy files, create links, install packages, run narrow setup steps, and explain the plan before touching the machine.\"}],[\"/why-16\",{\"id\":\"/why-16\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#the-problem\",\"content\":\"Most workstation setup starts as shell scripts. That works until the scripts need ordering, reuse, machine-specific branches, or a dry-run view.\"}],[\"/why-17\",{\"id\":\"/why-17\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#the-problem\",\"content\":\"Full configuration-management systems solve those problems, but they bring server/fleet assumptions, inventory models, roles, and runtime weight that feel oversized for one laptop or a small set of personal machines.\"}],[\"/why-18\",{\"id\":\"/why-18\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#the-problem\",\"content\":\"Boxfiles sits in that gap.\"}],[\"/why-19\",{\"id\":\"/why-19\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#local-first-setup\",\"content\":\"A Boxfiles workspace is a normal directory. Manifests live beside the files they manage, so a module can own both intent and assets:\"}],[\"/why-20\",{\"id\":\"/why-20\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#plan-before-apply\",\"content\":\"Boxfiles compiles manifests into a plan before execution. The plan shows what action provider will run, what target it affects, and whether the provider marks it as safe or unsafe.\"}],[\"/why-21\",{\"id\":\"/why-21\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#plan-before-apply\",\"content\":\"That makes review cheap. It also keeps parsing, context gathering, planning, and applying as separate phases.\"}],[\"/why-22\",{\"id\":\"/why-22\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#small-manifests\",\"content\":\"Manifests describe actions, dependencies, and conditions. Manifest IDs come from paths, so directory structure becomes the namespace:\"}],[\"/why-23\",{\"id\":\"/why-23\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#small-manifests\",\"content\":\"Dependencies stay explicit instead of hidden inside script order.\"}],[\"/why-24\",{\"id\":\"/why-24\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#capability-plugins\",\"content\":\"Plugins provide capabilities, not random command bags. A plugin can add context facts, action providers, or both.\"}],[\"/why-25\",{\"id\":\"/why-25\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#capability-plugins\",\"content\":\"That keeps built-ins small while still allowing local policy: package managers, OS facts, hardware checks, file operations, and project-specific setup can live behind typed providers.\"}],[\"/why-26\",{\"id\":\"/why-26\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-just-shell-scripts\",\"content\":\"Shell is still fine for one-off setup. Use it when the task is linear, single-platform, and obvious.\"}],[\"/why-27\",{\"id\":\"/why-27\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-just-shell-scripts\",\"content\":\"Boxfiles helps when you need:\"}],[\"/why-28\",{\"id\":\"/why-28\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-just-shell-scripts\",\"content\":\"discovery of many manifests\"}],[\"/why-29\",{\"id\":\"/why-29\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-just-shell-scripts\",\"content\":\"dependency ordering between modules\"}],[\"/why-30\",{\"id\":\"/why-30\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-just-shell-scripts\",\"content\":\"a plan before mutation\"}],[\"/why-31\",{\"id\":\"/why-31\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-just-shell-scripts\",\"content\":\"typed action config\"}],[\"/why-32\",{\"id\":\"/why-32\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-just-shell-scripts\",\"content\":\"reusable providers\"}],[\"/why-33\",{\"id\":\"/why-33\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-just-shell-scripts\",\"content\":\"context facts for OS, user, project, or plugin state\"}],[\"/why-34\",{\"id\":\"/why-34\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-just-shell-scripts\",\"content\":\"cross-platform setup across Windows, macOS, and Linux\"}],[\"/why-35\",{\"id\":\"/why-35\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-just-shell-scripts\",\"content\":\"conditional primitives like `when` instead of hand-rolled shell branches\"}],[\"/why-36\",{\"id\":\"/why-36\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-ansible\",\"content\":\"Ansible is powerful, mature, and better for remote hosts or teams already invested in its ecosystem.\"}],[\"/why-37\",{\"id\":\"/why-37\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-ansible\",\"content\":\"Boxfiles is smaller on purpose. It focuses on local workstation setup, local files, predictable manifest discovery, and a lighter plugin contract.\"}],[\"/why-38\",{\"id\":\"/why-38\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-nix\",\"content\":\"Nix is strong when you want deep reproducibility and accept its model, but that model is heavy for normal workstation setup.\"}],[\"/why-39\",{\"id\":\"/why-39\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#why-not-nix\",\"content\":\"Boxfiles avoids making every dotfile change a packaging exercise. It is for users who want incremental setup automation without turning their workstation into a full declarative operating-system project.\"}],[\"/why-40\",{\"id\":\"/why-40\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#what-boxfiles-is-not\",\"content\":\"Boxfiles is not a sandbox for untrusted code. Plugin code runs inside the trusted local config boundary.\"}],[\"/why-41\",{\"id\":\"/why-41\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#what-boxfiles-is-not\",\"content\":\"Boxfiles is not a perfect reproducibility system yet. Plugin lockfiles and stronger execution safety policy are deferred work.\"}],[\"/why-42\",{\"id\":\"/why-42\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#what-boxfiles-is-not\",\"content\":\"Boxfiles is not meant to hide every OS detail. Providers should abstract common operations, but workstation setup still has machine-specific edges.\"}],[\"/why-43\",{\"id\":\"/why-43\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#good-fit\",\"content\":\"Use Boxfiles when you want:\"}],[\"/why-44\",{\"id\":\"/why-44\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#good-fit\",\"content\":\"dotfiles plus actions\"}],[\"/why-45\",{\"id\":\"/why-45\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#good-fit\",\"content\":\"explicit setup order\"}],[\"/why-46\",{\"id\":\"/why-46\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#good-fit\",\"content\":\"reviewable plans\"}],[\"/why-47\",{\"id\":\"/why-47\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#good-fit\",\"content\":\"local manifests in YAML or TOML\"}],[\"/why-48\",{\"id\":\"/why-48\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#good-fit\",\"content\":\"plugins for missing capabilities\"}],[\"/why-49\",{\"id\":\"/why-49\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#good-fit\",\"content\":\"low ceremony over total control\"}],[\"/why-50\",{\"id\":\"/why-50\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#bad-fit\",\"content\":\"Reach for another tool when you need:\"}],[\"/why-51\",{\"id\":\"/why-51\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#bad-fit\",\"content\":\"remote fleet orchestration\"}],[\"/why-52\",{\"id\":\"/why-52\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#bad-fit\",\"content\":\"untrusted plugin isolation\"}],[\"/why-53\",{\"id\":\"/why-53\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#bad-fit\",\"content\":\"strict bit-for-bit reproducibility\"}],[\"/why-54\",{\"id\":\"/why-54\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#bad-fit\",\"content\":\"enterprise policy enforcement\"}],[\"/why-55\",{\"id\":\"/why-55\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#bad-fit\",\"content\":\"a general task runner with no provisioning model\"}],[\"/why-56\",{\"id\":\"/why-56\",\"page_id\":\"/why\",\"tags\":[],\"type\":\"text\",\"url\":\"/why#bad-fit\",\"content\":\"Boxfiles should stay boring: discover manifests, gather facts, compile a plan, then apply it when the user asks.\"}],[\"/plugins/builtin/copy\",{\"id\":\"/plugins/builtin/copy\",\"page_id\":\"/plugins/builtin/copy\",\"type\":\"page\",\"content\":\"copy\",\"breadcrumbs\":[\"Docs\",\"Plugins\",\"Builtin\"],\"tags\":[],\"url\":\"/plugins/builtin/copy\"}],[\"/plugins/builtin/copy-0\",{\"id\":\"/plu